    <question>
        <prompt>What characterized American neutrality before entering WWI?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Complete isolation from Europe</option>
            <option letter="b">Trading primarily with Germany</option>
            <option letter="c">Trading mainly with Allied powers</option>
            <option letter="d">Equal trade with both sides</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>During American "neutrality," the U.S. traded primarily with Allied powers due to the British naval blockade of Germany, showing the limits of true neutrality in practice.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Adamson Act affect railroad workers?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It banned unions</option>
            <option letter="b">It established the 8-hour workday</option>
            <option letter="c">It reduced wages</option>
            <option letter="d">It increased working hours</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Adamson Act of 1916 established an 8-hour workday for railroad workers with additional pay for overtime, representing a major victory for labor rights.</explanation>
